Do you just use https://www.cs.helsinki.fi/group/boi2016/doc/cppreference/reference/en.cppreference.com/w/c/string/byte/memcpy.html?

You don't need to use memcpy_s if you have guaranteed buffer space. You just add extra checks that will always succeed and could never be tested. And you have to actually check the return code of memcpy_s anyway.

friendly ping.

This change support current existing use cases in gBMC.
So we have an empty `BmcBlobEnumerateRx` struct at the beginning?

oh, are you seeing it as part of the `openBlob` function? It seems like Gerrit is doing weird stuff.

It is under the `enumerateBlob` function and yeah it has BmcBlobEnumerateRx in the beginning.

BmcBlobEnumerateRx only have a `crc` within it.

This replaces the following
```
auto reply = reinterpret_cast<struct BmcBlobEnumerateRx*>(replyCmdBuf);
reply->crc = 0;
```

Now I am wondering if I have an off by one error... since I inject data at the end instead of the beginning.
